    About

    Description

    Pablo Ruiz Picasso was a Spanish painter, sculptor, printmaker, ceramicist, and theatre designer who spent most of his adult life in France. Wikipedia
    Born: October 25, 1881, Málaga, Spain
    Died: April 8, 1973 (age 91 years), Mougins, France
    Periods: Cubism, Picasso's Blue Period, Surrealism, Modern art, MORE
    Influenced by: Vincent van Gogh, Paul Cézanne, MORE
    Children: Paloma Picasso, Paulo Picasso, Claude Pierre Pablo Picasso, Maya Widmaier-Picasso
    Spouse: Jacqueline Roque (m. 1961–1973), Olga Khokhlova (m. 1918–1955)
